<title>ITALY: Italy's Bologna sees Oct CPI at 3.9 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Bologna sees Oct CPI at 3.9 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>BOLOGNA, Italy 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Bologna said its October consumer price index stood at 0.2 percent month-on-month and 3.9 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In September, Bologna's inflation rate was 1.0 and 4.2 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Bologna is one of 10 Italian cities publishing inflation data on Monday and Tuesday.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 7.62 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to September 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.2   (1.0)     3.9  (4.2)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.3   (0.1)     2.4  (3.4)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   1.0   (0.1)     2.5  (3.0)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   1.2   (0.8)     6.1  (6.5)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0   (0.1)     2.9  (3.1)</p>
<p>    Health services		   1.3  (-0.2)     4.9  (4.0)</p>
<p>    Transportation		   -0.3   (0.0)     4.5  (4.5)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.1   (7.9)    10.2 (10.5)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.6   (0.0)     2.0  (1.4)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0   (0.1)     2.7  (2.7)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	-0.2  (-0.1)     1.1  (1.4)</p>
